		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />That's what is strange. PowerPak comes with "blank" .sav files, one 8K and one 32K so there is obvious <em>intention</em> for it to work, somehow.
<br />
<br />When I load up the ROM and point it at the save file it doesn't complain about the size (32K) but then again you might be able to point it at anything, I don't know how much validation PowerPak uses.
<br />
<br />Something I noticed last night is that contrary to what Bregalad said, I managed to get it working with a 128K ROM size, as opposed to the 256K that he said was required. I'll try making a 256K ROM and retest on PowerPak, just in case.
<br />
<br />But yes, at the end of the day, it could just be that iNES 2.0 is not supported.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
